.nr X
.if \nX=0 .ds x} intro D3DK "" "DDI/DKI" "\&"
.if \nX=1 .ds x} intro D3DK "" "DDI/DKI"
.if \nX=2 .ds x} intro D3DK "" "\&"
.if \nX=3 .ds x} intro "" "" "\&"
.TH \*(x}
.IX "\f4intro\fP(D3DK)"
.IX istart "DDI/DKI (Device Driver Interface/Driver\(enKernel Interface), kernel functions"
.IX istart driver, functions
.SH NAME
\f4intro\fP \- introduction to kernel utility routines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\f4#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/ddi.h>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This section describes the kernel utility functions available for use by device drivers.
Drivers must not call any kernel routines other than the ones described in this section.
.P
Unless otherwise stated, any kernel utility routine that sleeps will do so such that
signals will not interrupt the sleep.
.IX iend "DDI/DKI (Device Driver Interface/Driver\(enKernel Interface), kernel functions"
.ig
	null section helps create MasterToc
